ZPC–Möbius Engine

Purpose

Convert zero-centered oscillation into net positive drift by acting only near the inflection seam.

Not free energy.
Not magic extraction.

It is a rectification-and-bias engine:

* oscillation provides motion
* seam detection provides timing
* ZPC provides one-way capture
* feed-forward provides persistence

⸻

Core intuition

A system oscillates around zero:

x(t) \approx A\sin(\omega t) + \eta(t)

Normally, positive and negative phases cancel.

The ZPC changes that by:

1. detecting when the system is near a zero crossing or phase seam
2. capturing motion that points in the preferred direction
3. damping or ignoring the opposite phase
4. feeding a fraction of the gain back into the next cycle

So instead of:

+1 -1 +1 -1 = 0

you get:

+1 +0.2 +1.1 +0.1 +1.2 = \text{net positive drift}

