What makes it work

The whole system depends on three asymmetries:

1. Timing asymmetry

Only act near the seam.

2. Direction asymmetry

Only capture the preferred sign.

3. Memory asymmetry

Store gain and use it to tilt the future.

Without those, oscillation cancels.

⸻

Failure modes

This is important, because it tells you where the edge really is.

Too early

You act away from the seam, so the force gets wasted.

Too much force

You overpower the oscillator and destroy the subtle leverage.

Too much leakage

Nothing accumulates.

Wrong seam threshold

You capture noise, not inflection.

Overfeedback

The system becomes unstable and blows up instead of drifting.

